National Australia Bank Ltd &lt;NABA.S>said it lowered its benchmark prime lending rate to 18.25 pctfrom 18.5, effective today, but left its base rate at 18.5.    The benchmark reduction brings the rate into line with theprime rates of most of Australia's trading banks, includingthose of two of the other three major trading banks.    However, the rate is above the 18 pct - the lowest rulingrate - set by the other major, the Australia and New ZealandBanking Group Ltd &lt;ANZA.S>, on Friday and effective today.    The benchmark is based on short-term interest ratemovements while the base rate is tied to longer-term trends. REUTER&#3;